<paragraph id="8E39D07BB931FF97247EBAAFFBA45898" blockId="3.[113,772,1694,2038]" lastBlockId="3.[816,1474,1402,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
Characters important for distinguishing species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF9724B5BA8FFEA8589F" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1876" box="[186,306,1726,1749]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Euscorpius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9724B5BA8FFEA8589F" box="[186,306,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Euscorpius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: (1) trichobothriotaxy of the pedipalp patella, i. e., number of trichobothria in the external series 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF97247EBACFFF10595C" box="[113,138,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">eb</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF972496BACFFF215956" box="[153,187,1790,1820]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
eb 
<subScript id="1202D23EB931FF9724BCBB3FFF215956" attach="right" box="[179,187,1806,1820]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">a</subScript>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9724C6BACFFF77595C" box="[201,237,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">esb</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9724F3BACFFE81595F" box="[252,283,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">em</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF972525BACFFED2595F" box="[298,328,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">est</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF97258ABACFFE02595F" box="[389,408,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">et</emphasis>
, in combination with the number of ventral trichobothria; (2) shape and dimensions of the carapace, pedipalp and metasomal segments; (3) granulation and carination of metasomal segments; (4) coloration; and (5) pectinal tooth count. Two currently valid subgenera can be separated by the number of ventral trichobothria on the pedipalp chela manus, i. e., 
<quantity id="497E7D9EB931FF9725BABB8FFE79599C" box="[437,483,1982,2006]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF9725E0BB8FFDFD599F" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1876" box="[495,615,1982,2005]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Euscorpius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9725E0BB8FFDFD599F" box="[495,615,1982,2005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Euscorpius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A7C1B112B931FF97267CBB8FFD65599C" box="[627,767,1982,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and more than 
<quantity id="497E7D9EB931FF972512BBEFFED059BC" box="[285,330,2014,2038]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF97255ABBEFFD2C59BC" authority="Birula, 1917" authorityName="Birula" authorityYear="1917" box="[341,694,2014,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Polytrichobothrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF97255ABBEFFD8459BC" box="[341,542,2014,2038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Polytrichobothrius</emphasis>
Birula, 1917
</taxonomicName>
. These characters alone are not always sufficient for distinguishing a total of ca. 60 species, most of which were described or revalidated in the last two decades. Taxonomy of this genus remains complex and challenging. Recently, DNA analysis was suggested to be the only solution to this problem (see e. g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EA17AD8AB931FF97273FBA2BFBBD5879" author="PARMAKELIS" box="[816,1063,1562,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="728 - 748" refId="ref12658" refString="PARMAKELIS, A., I. STATHI, P. KOTSAKIOZI, S. POULIKARAKOU &amp; V. FET. 2013. Hidden diversity of Euscorpius (Scorpiones: Euscorpiidae) in Greece revealed by multilocus species-delimitation approaches. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 110: 728 - 748." type="journal article" year="2013">Parmakelis et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
; Fet et al., 2018). Based on our studies of this genus and the application of diagnostic characters to the related genus 
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF9727C6BA6AFB775839" authority="Karsch, 1881" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1881" box="[969,1261,1626,1651]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Megacormus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9727C6BA6AFBCE5838" box="[969,1108,1627,1650]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Megacormus</emphasis>
Karsch, 1881
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF9720F2BA6BFA165838" authorityName="Laurie" authorityYear="1896" box="[1277,1420,1626,1650]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Euscorpiidae</taxonomicName>
) and to the related family 
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF972017BA4BFAC558D8" authority="Kraepelin, 1905" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1905" box="[1048,1375,1658,1682]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpiopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scorpiopidae Kraepelin, 1905</taxonomicName>
, we here propose application of two additional characters to elucidate taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="4986ABF8B931FF9727B0BA8AFBAD5898" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1876" box="[959,1079,1723,1746]" class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Euscorpius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCF20C69B931FF9727B0BA8AFBAD5898" box="[959,1079,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Euscorpius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
